observations.recommendation:
We recommend that management to:
Intensify and implement measures to collect the past and demandable receivable.  Send demand letters and give specific deadline to compel the proponents to settle their accounts with the LGU;
Instruct concerned LGU officials/personnel on the periodic monitoring of funds transferred and utilized;
Institute legal action, if necessary, against defaulting POs; and
See to it that the requisites for entitlement to government funds by NGOs/POs shall be strictly complied with and ensure that the awarding of project is covered by a MOA of which the terms of reference under COA Circular No. 2007-001 are incorporated.

We recommend the Local Chief Executive to instruct the concerned official/personnel to:
Consolidate the PPMPs submitted by the end-user Offices;
Require the BAC to review carefully the contents of PPMPs and APP;
Implement strictly timelines on the posting and submission of procurement reports;
Establish procurement timelines in consonance with project schedules, including a cut-off date for processing requisitions and issuance of purchase orders to ensure receipt of most of the procured items in time for the project implementation;
Strict observance of RA 9184 and its IRR, and other existing rules and regulations on government procurement is enjoined as well as imposition of control measures to ensure that procurement is effected in an efficient, economical and effective manner that is most advantageous to the government and to prevent possible disallowances for such violation.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive to:
Identify authorized Local projects that necessitate the hiring of job order workers;
Align the hiring of job order personnel services with the Sanggunian authorized local projects.

Adhere to strictly to the policies and terms enunciated in the Economic Enterprise Code like PS Limitation;

Come up with a sound budget Management in accordance with its policy statement to be self-reliant and self-sustaining independent unit by considering circumstances like generating profits and enhancing good governance;

Intensify its collection efforts/process by following strictly policies and terms outlined in the Economic Enterprise Code for the rates and manner of collection.
